description: Try our easy to follow Fish fingers recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Fish fingers Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 600g cooked frozen crinkle cut chips, cooked (to serve)
2 cup fresh white breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200°C. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper. Cut fish into ‘fingers’ (about 10cm long x 3cm wide).

Place flour and breadcrumbs onto separate plates. Place egg into a shallow bowl. Dip each fish finger into flour, egg, then breadcrumbs, pressing on firmly. Arrange in a single layer on a baking tray.
Spray well with oil spray. Cook for 15–20 minutes or until golden and cooked through. Serve with chips, lettuce and lemon wedges.
